      <akn:section eId="sec_20_905">
        <akn:num>20-905</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Manner of presentation of claim.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_20-905_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A claimant shall present a claim against a decedent’s estate by delivering or mailing, return receipt requested, a written statement of the claim, verified in accordance with section 20-102:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_20-905_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A statement of a claim shall state:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_20-905_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Court may, in its discretion, disallow a claim, in whole or in part, if the claimant fails to comply with subsections (a) and (b) or with the personal representative’s reasonable requests for additional information.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
